import seaborn as sns
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    sns.scatterplot(x='x', y='y', data=data)
    plt.title('What is the distribution of x and y coordinates?', wrap=True)
    plt.xticks(rotation=90)
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker
def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    sns.regplot(x='x', y='y', data=data)
    plt.title('What is the relationship between x and y coordinates?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('x')
    plt.ylabel('y')
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.xticks(rotation=45)
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    else:
        plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    ax = sns.scatterplot(x="x", y="y", hue="distance", data=data)
    ax.set_title("What is the relationship between distances and x or y coordinates?", wrap=True)
    ax.xaxis.label.set_rotation(0)
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        ax.xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import matplotlib.ticker as ticker

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    plt.figure(figsize=(6, 6))
    data['quadrant'] = pd.cut(data['x'], [-1, 0, 1], labels=['left', 'right'])
    sns.boxplot(x='quadrant', y='distance', data=data)
    plt.title('What is the distribution of distances for each quadrant?', wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Quadrant')
    plt.ylabel('Distance')
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    if len(plt.xticks()[0]) > 20:
        plt.gca().xaxis.set_major_locator(ticker.MaxNLocator(20))
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
